<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>netstandard2.0</TargetFramework>
    <GeneratePackageOnBuild>true</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
    <Company>SuRGeoNix</Company>
    <Authors>SuRGeoNix</Authors>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>LGPL-3.0-or-later</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <Description>BitTorrent library for clients &amp; streaming purposes</Description>
    <PackageLicenseFile></PackageLicenseFile>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/SuRGeoNix/BitSwarm</PackageProjectUrl>
    <PackageIcon>BitSwarm.png</PackageIcon>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/SuRGeoNix/BitSwarm</RepositoryUrl>
    <RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
    <PackageTags>bitswarm torrent client streaming dht</PackageTags>
    <Copyright>Â© SuRGeoNix 2020</Copyright>
    <Version>2.1.0</Version>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>Beggar (Scheduler) &amp; DHT Algorithms Improvements

1. Re-design of DHT for faster bootstrap &amp; more peers from same nodes (2nd recursion) - Reducing also connect timeout on nodes
2. Re-design of BitSwarm's Beggar (Scheduler) - More speed &amp; less resources
3. Creating a Custom Threadpool (.NET's was causing issues - couldn't use different Threadpool on Parent UI Project - even if was imported in diffrent AppDomain with Proxy)
4. Peers will re-request pieces/blocks directly after finishing the previous ones
5. Adding Max Threads (Custom Threadpool) functionality to control the parallel new connection requests (more accurate)
6. Adding Sleep Mode functionality to reduce resources even more (It will not re-request DHT/Trackers, possible will auto-reduce MaxThreads in future)
7. Adding Download Limit functionality (not very accurate yet)
8. Fixing Issues with Peer's Receive Buffer Size, Torrent's Block Sizes etc.</PackageReleaseNotes>
    <FileVersion>2.1.0.0</FileVersion>
    <AssemblyVersion>2.1.0.0</AssemblyVersion>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <PropertyGroup Condition="'$(Configuration)|$(Platform)'=='Debug|AnyCPU'">
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <PropertyGroup Condition="'$(Configuration)|$(Platform)'=='Release|AnyCPU'">
    <AllowUnsafeBlocks>true</AllowUnsafeBlocks>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="BencodeNET" Version="3.1.4" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <None Include="..\Images\BitSwarm.png">
      <Pack>True</Pack>
      <PackagePath></PackagePath>
    </None>
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>